</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D7FF31FF73EF7488E9FEFC" blockId="169.[151,1436,289,601]" box="[151,738,289,313]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FF73EF748AE8FEFC" bold="true" box="[151,227,289,313]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" reason="1">Types.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="A037884970D7FF31FF0EEF748B59FEFC" box="[234,338,289,313]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Holotype</typeStatus>
queen from Yugoslovia (Miocene).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3796656070D7FF31FF23EF1089A9FD9C" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D7FF31FF23EF1089A9FD9C" blockId="169.[151,1436,289,601]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FF23EF108B44FE9B" bold="true" box="[199,335,325,350]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
Another species based on an impression fossil of a queen, the identity of this taxon remains obscure. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D7FF31FEE4EF3C8BD7FE44" author="Dalla Torre, C. G. de" box="[256,476,361,385]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" refId="ref110399" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. de (1893) Catalogus hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 7 Formicidae (Heterogyna). Leipzig: G. Engelmann, 289 pp." type="book" year="1893">Dalla Torre (1893)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FD4FEF3C8937FE44" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[683,828,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FD4FEF3C8937FE44" box="[683,828,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a treatment followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D7FF31FB90EF3C8F37FE44" author="Shattuck, S. O." box="[1140,1340,361,385]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref112320" refString="Shattuck, S. O. (1992 a) Review of the dolichoderine ant genus Iridomyrme x Mayr with descriptions of three new genera (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 31, 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="1992">
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FB90EF3C8EDDFE44" authority="Heterick &amp; Shattuck, 2011" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" box="[1140,1238,361,385]" genus="Shattuck" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Shattuck</taxonomicName>
(1992a)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D7FF31FAA8EF3C8AE4FE60" author="Mayr, G." pageId="169" pageNumber="170" pagination="47 - 62" refId="ref112018" refString="Mayr, G. (1867 b) Vorlaufige Studien uber die Radoboj-Formiciden, in der Sammlung der k. k. geologischen Reichsanstalt. Jahrbuch der k. k. Geologischen Reichsanstalt, 17, 47 - 62." type="journal article" year="1867">Mayr’s (1867b)</bibRefCitation>
figure of the 
<typeStatus id="A037884970D7FF31FE7BEFDB8BC4FE63" box="[415,463,398,422]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">type</typeStatus>
queen reveals little detail other than wing venation. While the general pattern is dolichoderine-like it differs from extant species of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FD36EFE48968FE0C" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[722,867,433,457]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FD36EFE48968FE0C" box="[722,867,433,457]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the Rs vein join M at 1m-cu, rather than basal to this cross vein, resulting in the cell enclosed by Rs, M and 2rs-m having three sides rather than four. A three-sided cell similar to Mayr’s (1869) figure for this species is present in some 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FBC8EFAC8ECFFDD4" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1068,1220,505,529]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dolichoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FBC8EFAC8ECFFDD4" box="[1068,1220,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Dolichoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(especially species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FE8BEC488BFBFDF0" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[367,496,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoclinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FE8BEC488BFBFDF0" box="[367,496,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Hypoclinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a condition not seen in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FCF5EC4889A9FDF0" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[785,930,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FCF5EC4889A9FDF0" box="[785,930,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because of this it would seem that this species would be better placed in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FE0FEC14888FFD9C" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[491,644,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dolichoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FE0FEC14888FFD9C" box="[491,644,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Dolichoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FCEEEC148991FD9C" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[778,922,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FCEEEC148991FD9C" box="[778,922,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
